{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed and did not retain a fix. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7294-fails-javac-compile-org.seleniumhq.selenium-selenium-support-4.20.0-e37ec918\n\nDespite the `fails-javac-compile` label, the preserved logs show the failure happens after `compileTestJava`, in test/native-image execution. In `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T14-25-57-628493Z.log`, `:nativeTest` fails with `AnnotationsTest` asserting the wrong locator string, `RelativeLocatorScriptTest` failing in `RelativeLocatorScript.<clinit>` with `NullPointerException`, and `ThreadGuardTest` failing with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for the `WebDriver` proxy. A later retry in `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T14-41-20-210627Z.log` still fails in `:test` because `RelativeLocatorScriptTest` expects `10` but Selenium serializes the distance as `10L`.\n\nThe metrics show why this still needs a person: `stats/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0/execution-metrics.json` ended with `status: failure`, identical starting/ending commit `0194180f350e42c3617de6527dafad3d0a4fc1b1`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`. The generation log `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-07T14-34-06-326906Z.log` shows a transient local edit to `tests/src/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-support/4.20.0/src/test/java/org_seleniumhq_selenium/selenium_support/RelativeLocatorScriptTest.java` to change the expected distance from `10` to `10L`, but that edit was not retained on the preserved branch. Later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T14-42-15-057144Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T14-44-04-891393Z.log` are `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, which suggests the automation found a local fix path but did not persist it.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Reconstruct and commit the missing transient test edits from `human-intervention-logs/org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-06-07T14-34-06-326906Z.log`, starting with the `RelativeLocatorScriptTest` `10` -> `10L` expectation change.\n2. Re-run the coordinate-scoped `test` and `nativeTest` lanes for `org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-support:4.20.0`, using the successful late reruns as the expected baseline.\n3. After the source changes are actually persisted, regenerate/publish the `4.20.0` stats so the issue no longer ends with `generated_loc: 0` and unavailable recorded coverage."}}
